-- Egypt Plans to Invite Bids for Two Wind Power Plants in 2011
-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2010-12-22T12:11:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/egypt-plans-to-invite-bids-for-two-wind-power-plants-in-2011.html
Egypt will invite bids for two 500-
megawatt wind power projects through the build-own-operate model
next year, Electricity Minister Hassan Younes said today.  The government will offer the projects in January and July
in the Gulf of Suez and will buy the energy produced for 20
years, he said in a faxed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
